SEGMENTS SPECIFICATIONS: (this is just here for the parser...)

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNA  Service String Advice

      Function: To define the characters selected for use as delimiters and indicators in the rest of the interchange
             that follows:
             The specifications in the Service string advice take precedence over the specifications for delimiters etc. in segment
             UNB. See clause 4.
             When transmitted, the Service string advice must appear immediately before the Interchange Header (UNB) segment
             and begin with the upper case characters UNA immediately followed by the six characters selected by the sender to
             define the delimiter characters., in sequence, the following functions

Ref.  Name                                        M/C Repr. Remarks

010   COMPONENT DATA ELEMENT SEPARATOR            M   an1
020   DATA ELEMENT SEPARATOR                      M   an1
030   DECIMAL NOTATION                            M   an1   Comma or full stop
040   RELEASE INDICATOR                           M   an1   If not used, insert space
050   Reserved for future use                     M   an1   Insert space
060   SEGMENT TERMINATOR                          M   an1

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNB  INTERCHANGE HEADER

      Function: To start, identify and specify an interchange


010   S001  SYNTAX IDENTIFIER                           M
      0001    Syntax identifier                         M   a4       a3, upper case
      0002    Syntax version number                     M   n1

020   S002  INTERCHANGE SENDER                          M
      0004    Sender identification                     M   an..35
      0007    Identification code qualifier             C   an..4
      0008    Address for reverse routing               C   an..14

030   S003  INTERCHANGE RECIPIENT                       M
      0010    Recipient Identification                  M   an..35
      0007    Identification code qualifier             C   an..4
      0014    Routing address                           C   an..14

040   S004  DATE/TIME OF PREPARATION                    M
      0017    Date                                      M   n6       YYMMDD
      0019    Time                                      M   n4       HHMM

050   0020  INTERCHANGE CONTROL REFERENCE               M   an..14

060   S005  RECIPIENTS REFERENCE, PASSWORD              C
      0022    Recipient's reference/password            M   an..14
      0025    Recipient's reference/password qualifier  C   an2

070   0026  APPLICATION REFERENCE                       C   an..14

080   0029  PROCESSING PRIORITY CODE                    C   a1

090   0031  ACKNOWLEDGEMENT REQUEST                     C   n1

100   0032  COMMUNICATIONS AGREEMENT ID                 C   an..35

110   0035  TEST INDICATOR                              C   n1

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNZ  INTERCHANGE TRAILER

      Function: To end and check the completeness of an interchange


010   0036  INTERCHANGE CONTROL COUNT                 M    n..6

020   0020  INTERCHANGE CONTROL REFERENCE             M    an..14   Shall be identical to 0020 in UNB

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNG  FUNCTIONAL GROUP HEADER

      Function: To head, identify and specify a Functional Group


010   0038  FUNCTIONAL GROUP IDENTIFICATION           M    an..6

020   S006  APPLICATION SENDER'S IDENTIFICATION       M
      0040    Sender identification                   M    an..35
      0007    Sender identification qualifier         C    an..4

030   S007  APPLICATION RECIPIENTS IDENTIFICATION     M
      0044    Recipient's identification              M    an..35
      0007    Recipient's identification qualifier    C    an..4

040   S004  DATE/TIME OF PREPARATION                  M
      0017    Date                                    M    n6       YYMMDD
      0019    Time                                    M    n4       HHMM

050   0048  FUNCTIONAL GROUP REFERENCE NUMBER         M    an..14

060   0051  CONTROLLING AGENCY                        M    an..2

070   S008  MESSAGE VERSION                           M
      0052    Message version number                  M    n..3
      0054    Message release number                  C    n..3
      0057    Association assigned Code               C    an..6

080   0058  APPLICATION PASSWORD                      C    an..14

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNE  FUNCTIONAL GROUP TRAILER

      Function: To end and check the completeness of a Functional Group


010   0060  NUMBER OF MESSAGES                        M    n..6

020   0048  FUNCTIONAL GROUP REFERENCE NUMBER         M    an..14   Shall be identical to 0048 in UNG

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNH  MESSAGE HEADER

      Function: To head, identify and specify a Message

010   0062  MESSAGE REFERENCE NUMBER                  M   an..14

020   S009  MESSAGE IDENTIFIER                        M
      0065    Message type                            M   an..6
      0052    Message version number                  M   n..3
      0054    Message release number                  C   n..3
      0051    Controlling agency                      C   an..2
      0057    Association assigned code               C   an..6

030   0068  COMMON ACCESS REFERENCE                   C   an..35

040   S010  STATUS OF THE TRANSFER                    C
      0070    Sequence of transfers                   M   n..2
      0073    First and last transfer                 C   a1

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNT  MESSAGE TRAILER

      Function: To end and check the completeness of a Message

010   0074  NUMBER OF SEGMENTS IN THE MESSAGE         M   n..6

020   0062  MESSAGE REFERENCE NUMBER                  M   an..14   Shall be identical to 0062 in UNH

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      TXT  TEXT

      Function: To give information in addition to that in other segments in the service message, as required

010   0077  TEXT REFERENCE CODE                       C   an3

020   0078  FREE FORM TEXT                            M   an..70

----------------------------------------------------------------------

      UNS  SECTION CONTROL

      Function: To separate Header, Detail and Summary sections of a message

010   0081  SECTION IDENTIFICATION                    M   a1

